	  <title>Modeling Velocities - Exercises</title>
	
	  <exercise>
		    <problem>
         <problem.body>
			         <para>
               <para.body>An airplane is moving east with a speed of 800km/hour relative to the surrounding air. The surrounding air is moving north-east with a speed of 150km/hour relative to the ground, carrying the plane with it. Find the velocity and the speed of the airplane relative to the ground.</para.body>
            </para>
			
			         <para align="center">
               <para.body>
                  <media xmlns="" type="image" active="1" inline="0">
                     <img src="ims/VelocitySuperposition.gif" height="173" width="441">
                        <image.mapping>
                           <area xmlns="Compositor" shape="rect" coords="217,39,417,53">
					                         <info>
                                 <info.caption>
                                    <caption>What does the blue arrow mean?</caption>
                                 </info.caption>
						
						                           <para>
                                    <para.body>This vector represents the velocity of the aircraft relative to the surrounding air.</para.body>
                                 </para>
					                         </info>
				                       </area>
                           <area xmlns="Compositor" shape="poly" coords="135,115,155,111,219,39,193,35">
					                         <info>
                                 <info.caption>
                                    <caption>What does the green arrow mean?</caption>
                                 </info.caption>
						
						                           <para>
                                    <para.body>This vector represents the velocity of the air relative to the ground.</para.body>
                                 </para>
					                         </info>
				                       </area>
                           <area xmlns="Compositor"
                                 shape="poly"
                                 coords="157,113,161,121,425,47,369,51,159,107">
					                         <info>
                                 <info.caption>
                                    <caption>What does the red arrow mean?</caption>
                                 </info.caption>
						
						                           <para>
                                    <para.body>This vector represents the velocity of the aircraft relative to the ground.</para.body>
                                 </para>
					                         </info>
				                       </area>
                        </image.mapping>
                     </img>
                  </media>
			            </para.body>
            </para>
		       </problem.body>
      </problem>
		    <approach version="1">
			      <answer.exercise>
            <answer.exercise.block>
               <answer.exercise.block.body>
				              <ul>
					                <li>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>Velocity of the air plane relative to ground: <math>
                                 <latex>(800 + 150\cdot \tfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}} , 150\cdot \tfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </li>
					
					                <li>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>Speed relative to the ground: approximately <math>
                                 <latex>912.253</latex>
                              </math> [km/h]</para.body>
                        </para>
                     </li>
				              </ul>
			            </answer.exercise.block.body>
            </answer.exercise.block>
         </answer.exercise>
			      <solution.hint>
				        <para>
               <para.body>Use the vector diagram above to model the velocity of the plane relative to the ground.</para.body>
            </para>
			      </solution.hint>
			      <solution>
            <solution.body>
				           <para>
                  <para.body>Let a vector of length 1 represent the speed of 1km/h. Then the velocity of the air relative to the ground is represented by the vector</para.body>
               </para>
				
				           <para align="center">
                  <para.body>
                     <subordinate>
                        <hot>
                           <math>
                              <latex>\mathbf{a}\ :=\ 150\cdot \dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\cdot (1,1)</latex>
                           </math>
                        </hot>
                        <info>
                           <info.caption>
                              <caption>Explanation</caption>
                           </info.caption>
						
						                     <para>
                              <para.body>The vector <math>
                                    <latex>(1,1)</latex>
                                 </math> has length <math>
                                    <latex>| (1,1) | = \sqrt{2}</latex>
                                 </math>. Therefore the vector <math>
                                    <latex>\tfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\cdot (1,1)</latex>
                                 </math> has length <math>
                                    <latex>1</latex>
                                 </math> and points North-West. Finally, the vector <math>
                                    <latex>\mathbf{a}</latex>
                                 </math> has length <math>
                                    <latex>150</latex>
                                 </math> and points North-West. It therefore represents the velocity of the air relative to the ground.</para.body>
                           </para>
					                   </info>
                     </subordinate>
				              </para.body>
               </para>
				
				           <para>
                  <para.body>The velocity of the airplane relative to the air is represented by the vector</para.body>
               </para>
				
				           <math.display>
					             <latex>\mathbf{b}\ :=\ 800 \cdot (1,0)</latex>
				           </math.display>
				
				           <para>
                  <para.body>Therefore the velocity vector of the aircraft relative to the ground is</para.body>
               </para>
				
				           <table align="center">
					             <row>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>\mathbf{v}</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>=</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>\mathbf{a} + \mathbf{b}</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
					             </row>
					             <row>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body> </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>=</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>150\cdot tfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\cdot (1,1)\ +\ 800\cdot (1,0)</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
					             </row>
					             <row>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body> </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>=</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>(800 + 150\cdot tfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}, 150\cdot tfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}})</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
					             </row>
				           </table>
				
				           <para>
                  <para.body>Consequently, the speed of the aircraft relative to the ground is</para.body>
               </para>
				
				           <table align="center">
					             <row>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>| \mathbf{v} |</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>=</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>\sqrt{ ( 800 + 150 \cdot \tfrac{1}{ \sqrt{2} } )^2\ +\ (150\cdot \tfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}})^2}</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
					             </row>
					             <row>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body> </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>\approx</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>\sqrt{ 820955.6275 + 11250 }</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
					             </row>
					             <row>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body> </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>\approx</latex>
                              </math>
                           </para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
						               <cell>
                        <para>
                           <para.body>
                              <math>
                                 <latex>912.253</latex>
                              </math> [km/h]</para.body>
                        </para>
                     </cell>
					             </row>
				           </table>
			         </solution.body>
         </solution>
		    </approach>
